# Agent Teams

## Overview

Run a manager-worker pattern. Stay as the lead agent, build the execution plan, assign narrow responsibilities to subagents, and return one integrated answer to the user.

Assume the user is the boss. Your job is to convert an ambiguous boss request into a concrete delivery pipeline without making the user manage the internal team.

## Operating Model

Use this role split unless the task clearly needs a different shape:

1. Lead agent: Understand the request, identify constraints, define success criteria, choose the execution strategy, and own final integration.
2. Explorer agents: Answer specific read-only questions about the codebase, documents, or requirements.
3. Worker agents: Implement bounded changes or produce concrete artifacts with explicit ownership.
